AB  - ... A multi-purpose urban reservoir protects against flooding, boosts water supply, and enhances downtown area. Twenty years in development, Singapore's Marina Barrage today is providing three main benefits: as a tidal barrier and pumping station for flood control, as a reservoir for augmented water supply serving some 4.8 million people, and as a new lifestyle attraction around the reservoir and tributary rivers in the heart of urban Singapore. Despite the challenges - complex system simulation and engineering to assure both water control and water quality, the sheer scale of the barrage crest gates and pumps, and careful construction in one of the world's busiest port areas Marina Barrage is performing as it was intended to do. It offers a model of integrated and sustainable water management in one of the world's great urban centres.
