TY  - Conference
TI  - Coastal climate change adaptation - Building coastal engineering and management capacity in a remote pacific Island
JO  - Coasts And Ports 2013
PY  - 2013
VL  - NA
IS  - NA
AB  - Kiribati is a nation of low lying Pacific Islands and one of the most vulnerable countries in the world to the effects of climate change. With the majority of the nation's capital island, South Tarawa, being less than three meters above sea level and less than 500m in width, it is at particularly high risk of sustaining significant damage to key government and community infrastructure from coastal erosion and inundation. Coastal management in Kiribati has largely been undertaken on a reactive basis by government. However, in the face of rising sea level and increased storminess, it is crucial that Kiribati transitions to a proactive coastal management approach. In response to this demand, the Kiribati Adaptation Program funded the placement of a Coastal Engineer within the Ministry of Public Works and Utilities (MPWU) to build coastal management and engineering capacity. This placement assisted and promoted the development of Ministry personnel to identify and prioritise areas at high risk of coastal erosion and inundation, assess the suitability of coastal management options and to improve their coastal defence construction techniques. Four pilot sites were identified and prioritised for immediate coastal protection. These sites required the design and construction of hard coastal defences to improve resilience against common failure mechanisms that have occurred in the past. The designs also addressed the challenges of working in a remote environment, extreme weather conditions and availability of plant and materials. The pilot sites provided an opportunity to develop internal capability and capacity of the MPWU to address such issues in the future, encouraging the local community to be self-reliant. This project highlights the significant community benefits to be gained through considering sustainable coastal climate change engineering solutions that are tailored to build on local capability and practices.
